---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Prose from '../components/Prose.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — bellsoftware" description="Senior software engineer at Getty Images. Platform reliability, frontend infrastructure, and building autonomous AI agent systems." active="about">
  <article>
    <header class="article-header">
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>
    <Prose>
      <p>
        I'm a senior software engineer at Getty Images, working on
        <strong>platform reliability</strong>, <strong>frontend infrastructure</strong>, and migrating legacy <code>Rails</code> systems to
        <code>Nest.js</code> and <code>TypeScript</code>. My expertise spans several critical domains including <strong>site reliability engineering</strong>, <strong>information security</strong>, and
        reducing <strong>tech debt</strong> across <strong>microfrontends</strong> at scale.
      </p>
      <p>
        I came to engineering non-traditionally. International studies and philosophy degree,
        career transition bootcamp, then ten years building up from there. But I was already
        thinking this way before the switch: I taught myself <code>Ruby</code> at my old job to wrangle large
        datasets and automate the tedious parts away. I've always been drawn to making work easier
        and clearer for myself and the people around me.
      </p>
      <p>
        That instinct translates well to building systems with AI. Outside work, I build autonomous AI agent systems:
        <strong>multi-agent architectures</strong> with task-specialized <strong>subagents</strong>, local LLM inference,
        and tool-using agents wired into real workflows. I'm interested in how <strong>agentic systems</strong> change
        the shape of software: what becomes a skill vs. a service, how context flows between agents, and where
        determinism still matters. I wrote about this in <a href="/writing/the-work-isnt-prompting">The work isn't prompting</a>.
      </p>
    </Prose>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-24);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    article {
      padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-16);
    }
  }

  .article-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .article-header h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.022em;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .article-header h1 {
      font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    }
  }
</style>
